      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HIS FERNANDO (1) comes off an average performance last start when sixth at this track over 400m behind Tornado Ethics (22.81) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money the start prior. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Has ability and looks hard to stop. TERRELL BANNER (3) scored last time out by 0.8 lengths at Richmond over 401m (23.13). Missed the frame only look here. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Must be included in calculations. JILLIBY SCOTTY (5) showed good early burn and was there until turning but swamped late to finish 6th at Richmond Straight in Grade 5 company. Expected to feature in the finish. AUSSIE RATTLER (2) found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into second last time out (22.98) over 400m at The Gardens. Safe beginner who should be prominent to the first bend.",
